    <thetext>Many languages support multiline strings through a heredoc type syntax.

Python:
longStr = &quot;&quot;&quot;This
is 
a 
multiline
string&quot;&quot;&quot;

C#:
string longStr = @&quot;This
is
a
multiline
string&quot;;

PHP:
$foo = &lt;&lt;EOF
This
is
a
multiline
string
EOF

ECMAScript supports multiline strings, but the continuation character can be cumbersome

var longString = &quot;This\
is\
a\
multiline\
string&quot;;

If you forget the continuation character, it can cause confusion trying to determine where the issue is.</thetext>
